abstract: Google said it planned a $1 billion campus just south of the West Village that would enable it to double its local work force over a decade.

lead_paragraph: Thereâ€™s a large spot reserved in the popular imagination for the Platonic ideal of an out-of-control market, a stunning collective enthusiasm that was bound to end in ruin: the tulip mania of the Netherlands, which ended in 1637. Tulips, a newly fashionable luxury item, temporarily became more valuable than houses â€” until, obviously, the inevitable market correction, which ruined fortunes and tore a nation apart.

abstract: About a dozen executives at the company are expected to be arrested on Tuesday by the Manhattan district attorney on fraud, theft and bribery charges.
snippet: About a dozen executives at the company are expected to be arrested on Tuesday by the Manhattan district attorney on fraud, theft and bribery charges.
lead_paragraph: More than 18 months ago, the Manhattan district attorneyâ€™s office opened yet another investigation into fraud in the cityâ€™s $62 billion construction industry, this one involving Bloomberg L.P., the financial information and media company owned by former Mayor Michael Bloomberg, who is considering running for president in 2020.
